{
  "_comment": [
    "List definitions, resolved by fetch_lists.py. Two kinds:",
    "  tmdb    - a public TMDB list, pulled by id (exact join on tmdb_id).",
    "  curated - hand-picked films as [title, year]. Written as title+year rather",
    "            than opaque ids so the set is auditable in review, and so a wrong",
    "            entry fails loudly at resolve time instead of silently pointing at",
    "            the wrong film.",
    "min_coverage gates what ships: our catalog is TMDB's top ~5000 by vote count,",
    "so arthouse-leaning lists match poorly (Golden Lion 11%, Palme d'Or 30%) and",
    "would ship as a misleading stub. Measured coverage is printed per list."
  ],

